    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter enabling autocompletion i noticed that after reaching the edge of the screen, there is some sort of a cursor lag where the cursor appears behind typed characters.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/616fde5b-40b1-4c66-98ae-54e3b409bbf3\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. launch neovim with these settings:\n```\nvim.opt.wrap = false\nvim.o.complete = '.,w,b,o'\nvim.o.autocomplete = true\nvim.o.autocompletedelay = 250\n```\n\n2. open a file with a long line\n3. split the window so that the line reaches the other end of the window\n4. press 'A' and start typing any string that activates a completion popup menu\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe cursor shouldn't appear behind typed characters.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-589+gdd65b4b152\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nhaven't tried, because vim doesn't have autocompletion\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nfedora 44\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.27.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt from source",
